|Metaphor.Alias.Name=ACTION IS SELF-PROPELLED MOTION
|Metaphor.Alias.Provenance=PITF
|Metaphor.Alias.Page no=191
}}
|Comments="actions are seen as movements that an agent carries out under the agent's own force" (PITF, p. 187)
The current metaphor is defined for motion that involves a change in the mover's location (i.e. motion along a path).
|Family=Location Event Structure Metaphor, Action is Motion metaphors, Grady Primary Metaphors, 
